<%= provide(:title, 'About') %>
<div class="row">
  <div class="span8 offset1 well">
    <h2>Why is this all?</h2>
    <br/>
    <p>Ever wondered, how
       <%= link_to "Google Autocomplete", "http://support.google.com/websearch/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=106230", :target => "_blank" %>
       works? How it decides which phrases to offer?
    <br/>
    <p>Maybe you were just curious how many
       <%= link_to "gems", "http://www.autocompletefail.com", :target => "_blank" %>
       <%= link_to "like", "http://failblog.org/tag/autocomplete-me", :target => "_blank" %>
       <%= link_to "these", "http://www.searchenginepeople.com/blog/google-autocomplete-fails.html", :target => "_blank" %>
       are remain to be found?
    <br/>
    <p>This tool goes through the list of the most popular English words and feeds them to
       Google Autocomplete API. Results are updated daily, and if we're finding something
       that looks like a website, we put it in a separate table.
    <br/>
    <p>The results can be used as a basis for a marketing/PR campaign, to predict what is going
       to be interesting, and just to
       <%= link_to "have fun", "http://www.vasil-y.com/1/category/google-fun/1.html", :target => "_blank" %>.
    <br/>
    <br><h3>Resources</h3><br>
    <ul class="unstyled">
      <li><%= link_to "Blog", "http://vasil-y.com", :target => "_blank" %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "GitHub", "https://github.com/vasily-ponomarev", :target => "_blank" %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Habrahabr (in Russian)", "http://habrahabr.ru/users/vponomarev/topics", :target => "_blank" %></li>
    </ul>
    <br><h3>Contacts</h3><br>
    <address>
      <strong>Help and Suggestions</strong><br>
      <%= mail_to "contact@global-trend-finder.com" %>
    </address>
  </div>
</div>
